def: Any one of several species of very brilliant South Americanhumming birds, having a very long and deeply-forked tail; as, theblue-tailed sylph (Cynanthus cyanurus).
Of or pertaining to an urn; effected by an urn or urns. "Urnalinterments." Sir T. Browne.
Any large Old World lizard of the genus Varanus; esp., theEgyptian species (V. Niloticus), which is useful because it devoursthe eggs and young of the crocodile. It is sometimes five or six feetlong.
To start suddenly aside through fright or suspicion; -- saidespecially of horses.
Of the nature of agate, or containing agate.
A condition in which the prepuce, after being retracted behindthe glans penis, is constricted there, and can not be brought forwardinto place again.
Liable to, or deserving, vituperation, or severe censure.
One who, or that which, squirts.
See Dike. The spelling dyke is restricted by some to thegeological meaning.
